==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seignior
<hw>Seign"ior</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>seignor</ets>, F. <ets>seigneur</ets>, cf. It. <ets>signore</ets>,
Sp. <ets>se⟦ntil⟧or</ets> from an objective case of L. <ets>senier</ets>
elder. See <er>Senior</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A lord; the lord of
a manor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A title of honor or of address in the South of
Europe, corresponding to <xex>Sir</xex> or <xex>Mr</xex>. in
English.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grand Seignior</b></col>, <cd>the sultan of
Turkey.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seigniorage</ent>⟦br⟧
